
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `fc-cat` baraye chap kardane (display) chand font az file-haye cache font config estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikone ke etela'ati raje' be font-ha, mesle name va masir-haye onha ro bebinid. Agar shoma barname-nevis hastid ya be font-ha alaghe darid, in dastoor baratoon mofid khahad bood.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `fc-cat` --> 📜 Chap kardane hameye font-ha az file-haye cache.
    🔹 `fc-cat pattern` --> 👀 Chap kardane font-hayee ke ba `pattern` motabeghat daran. Masalan `fc-cat "Sans"` hameye font-haye "Sans" ra chap mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ fc-cat

    🔹 Namayesh hameye font-haye mojood dar cache-ha.

    $ fc-cat "Arial:style=Bold"

    🔹 Namayesh font Arial ba style Bold.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ fc-cat | grep "family:"

    🔹 Chap kardane hameye font-ha va estefade az `grep` baraye jostejoo va namayesh khat-hayee ke shamel "family:" hastand, ke name khanvade font ra neshon midahad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `fc-cat` command is used to display multiple fonts from the font config cache files. This command helps you view information about fonts, such as their names and paths. If you're a developer or interested in fonts, this command can be useful.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `fc-cat` --> 📜 Display all fonts from the cache files.
    🔹 `fc-cat pattern` --> 👀 Display fonts that match the `pattern`. For example, `fc-cat "Sans"` will display all "Sans" fonts.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ fc-cat

    🔹 Display all fonts available in the caches.

    $ fc-cat "Arial:style=Bold"

    🔹 Display the Arial font with the Bold style.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ fc-cat | grep "family:"

    🔹 Display all fonts and use `grep` to search and show lines containing "family:", which shows the font family name.
